						<summary>

						<p>This is stated to be the composition of a poet by name Kālakālaṉ Īḻattaraiyaṉ. It is a verse describing the beauties of Tirukkaḍavūr with its <hi rend="italic">champaka</hi> groves humming with bees and with the rolling Kāvēri river, the favourite place of residence of god Kālakāladēva.</p>						

						</summary>
